ZORRO (1957) 24-27

 24. The New Commandante   3/20/1958 
The new, loyal commandante, Captain Toledano poses a threat to The Eagle and his men. They plot against him, using his wife as an unknowing pawn in their scheme. Diego, as Zorro, must save the loyal captain and fight for his life at the same time.
  Guest star: Vinton Hayworth (Magistrado Carlos Galindo), Suzanne Lloyd (Raquel Toledano) , Anthony George (Peralta), Peter Adams (Captain Arturo Toledano)

25. The Fox and the Coyote    3/27/1958 
Magistrado Galindo plots to steal the army&#039;s gunpowder for The Eagle&#039;s schemes, by planning a horserace to distract the guards and the captain. Zorro rides to stop the gunpowder from falling into their hands.
  Guest star: Vinton Hayworth (Magistrado Carlos Galindo), Suzanne Lloyd (Raquel Toledano) , Peter Adams (Captain Arturo Toledano), Armand Alzamora (Figueroa)

26. Adios, Senor Magistrado   4/3/1958 
The captain gains unexpected help from Zorro when he stands accused of murder.
  Guest star: Vinton Hayworth (Magistrado Carlos Galindo) , Peter Adams (Captain Arturo Toledano), Armand Alzamora (Figueroa)

27. The Eagle&#039;s Brood   4/10/1958 
With the magistrate&#039;s death, The Eagle becomes more bold in his plan. He sends the captain on a wild-goose chase while his own men smuggle gunpowder into the pueblo. However, Zorro is not tricked--and again proves that he truly is &#039;The Fox.&#039;
  Guest star: Charles Korvin (Jose Sebastian Varga-"The Eagle"), Suzanne Lloyd (Raquel Toledano) , Peter Adams (Captain Arturo Toledano), Michael Pate (Salvador Quintana), Peter Mamakos (Enrique Fuentes)
